cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about contextual word embeddings, which are widely used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the neural architectures used to learn these embeddings, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The study of how the representations vary with network depth could also relate to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions using these embeddings for tasks such as sentiment analysis and named entity recognition, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as well.
